`,n.jsx(e.h2,{children:"A Deep look into the Controller Runtime"}),`
`,n.jsx(e.p,{children:"Controller Runtime is a set of libraries and tools in the Kubernetes ecosystem, designed to simplify the process of building and managing Kubernetes controllers and operators. It’s part of the Kubernetes Operator SDK and is widely used to develop custom controllers that can manage Kubernetes resources, including custom resources (CRDs)."}),`
`,n.jsxs(e.p,{children:["Controller Runtime provides a structured framework for controller logic, handling many of the lower-level details of working with the Kubernetes API, so developers can focus more on defining the behavior of the controller and less on boilerplate code. It is written in Go and builds on the Kubernetes ",n.jsx(e.code,{children:"client-go"})," libraries."]}),`
